pr_body:
Scikit-learn's GradientBoostingClassifier fails in
if gbm:
    # do something
We instead test
if gbm is not None:
    # do something

@bear Sorry for the duplicate branches, but here's the partial data and tests for the API using responses ( cf #273 ). These tests work without modification to the API in any way -- just testing functionality that already works out of the box. This doesn't get us to 100% coverage, but from my setup it's from about 28% to 46%. 

There are some other changes that I'd like to see, which cause #273 to fail, but I don't want to mix proposed changes to the API and object models with testing that gets us better coverage in the meantime (my thought being the unobjectionable stuff is useful in its own regard as 3.0rc1 moves out of candidate). 

Let me know what you think of this strategy and I'll modify as necessary. Thanks for letting me contribute!

After certain operations a Dataset cannot be pickled any more. This PR fixes this by making sure the dataset is cleaned when a pickle request is done.

Also see #428 

@giulioungaretti  @core

Fix code for Keysight 34461A and split the driver depending on the model, like in #772 
Also it automatically detect if the digitizer option is installed.

